  "abstract": "ICSV 145', a witchweed (Striga asiatica L. Kuntze) resistant\r\nsorghum [Sorghum bicolor (L.) Moench] (Reg. no 128) (PI\r\n522247) cultivar was developed by the International Crops\r\nResearch Institute for the Semi-Arid Tropics (ICRISAT),\r\nPatancheru P.O. Andhra Pradesh 502 324, India. ICSV 145\r\n(ICRISAT Sorghum Cultivar 145) has been specifically bred\r\nfor resistance to the white flowered strain of S. asiatica that grows in India.",
